#MEM id=finance-based-pricing-advisor source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Finance/felix/skills/executive-operations/finance-based-pricing-advisor/SKILL.md
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|name: fin-based-pricing-advisor
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|description: >-
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|Evaluate pricing changes using ARPU, conversion, churn risk, NRR, and payback. Use when deciding whether a pricing move should ship.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|version: 1.0.0
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|platforms: []
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|metadata:
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|hermes:
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|tags: [fin, pl, runway, cac, ltv, mrr, margin, roi]
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|intent: Evaluate the **financial impact** of pricing changes (price increases, new tiers, add-ons, discounts) using ARPU/ARPA analysis, conversion impact, churn risk, NRR effects, and CAC payback impl
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|type: interactive
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|best_for:
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|scenarios:
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|Evaluate the **financial impact** of pricing changes (price increases, new tiers, add-ons, discounts) using ARPU/ARPA analysis, conversion impact, churn risk, NRR effects, and CAC payback implications
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**What this is:** Financial impact evaluation for pricing decisions you're already considering.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**What this is NOT:** Comprehensive pricing str design, value-based pricing frameworks, willingness-to-pay research, competitive positioning, psychological pricing, packaging architecture, or monetiza
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|This skill assumes you have a specific pricing change in mind and need to evaluate its financial viability.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|A systematic approach to evaluate pricing changes financially:
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|1. **Revenue Impact** — How does this change ARPU/ARPA?
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Direct revenue lift from price increase
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Revenue loss from reduced conversion or increased churn
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Net revenue impact
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|2. **Conversion Impact** — How does this affect trial-to-paid or sales conversion?
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Higher prices may reduce conversion rate
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Better packaging may improve conversion
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Test assumptions
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|3. **Churn Risk** — Will existing customers leave due to price change?
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Grandfathering str (protect existing customers)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Churn risk by segment (SMB vs. enterprise)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Churn elasticity (how sensitive are customers to price?)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|4. **Expansion Impact** — Does this create or block expansion opportunities?
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- New premium tier = upsell path
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Usage-based pricing = expansion as customers grow
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Add-ons = cross-sell opportunities
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|5. **CAC Payback Impact** — Does pricing change affect unit economics?
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Higher ARPU = faster payback
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Lower conversion = higher effective CAC
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Net effect on LTV:CAC ratio
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Direct monetization changes:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Price increase (raise prices for all customers or new customers only)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- New premium tier (create upsell path)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Paid add-on (monetize previously free feature)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Usage-based pricing (charge for consumption)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Discount strategies:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Annual prepay discount (improve cash flow)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Volume discounts (larger deals)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Promotional pricing (temporary price reduction)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Packaging changes:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Feature bundling (combine features into tiers)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Unbundling (separate features into add-ons)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Pricing metric change (seats → usage, or vice versa)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- **Not value-based pricing:** This evaluates a proposed change, not "what should we charge?"
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- **Not WTP research:** This analyzes impact, not "what will customers pay?"
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- **Not competitive positioning:** This is financial analysis, not market positioning
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- **Not packaging architecture:** This evaluates one change, not redesigning all tiers
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Use this when:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- You have a specific pricing change to evaluate (e.g., "Should we raise prices 20%?")
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- You need to quantify revenue, churn, and conversion trade-offs
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- You're deciding between pricing change options (test A vs. B)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- You need to present pricing change impact to leadership or board
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Don't use this when:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- You're designing pricing str from scratch (use value-based pricing frameworks)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- You haven't validated willingness-to-pay (do customer research first)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- You don't have baseline metrics (ARPU, churn, conversion rates)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Change is too small to matter (<5% price change, <10% of customers affected)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|Use [`workshop-facilitation`](../workshop-facilitation/SKILL.md) as the default interaction protocol for this skill.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|It defines:
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- ses heads-up + entry mode (Guided, ctx dump, Best guess)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- one-question turns with plain-language prompts
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- progress labels (for example, ctx Qx/8 and Scoring Qx/5)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- interruption handling and pause/resume behavior
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- numbered recommendations at dec points
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- quick-select numbered rsp options for regular questions (include `Other (specify)` when useful)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|This file defines the domain-specific assessment cnt. If there is a conflict, follow this file's domain logic.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|This interactive skill asks **up to 4 adaptive questions**, offering **3-5 enumerated options** at dec points.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**agt asks:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|"Let's evaluate the financial impact of your pricing change. Please provide:
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Current pricing:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Current ARPU or ARPA
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Current pricing tiers (if applicable)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Current monthly churn rate
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Current trial-to-paid conversion rate (if relevant)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Proposed pricing change:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- What change are you considering? (price increase, new tier, add-on, etc.)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- New pricing (if known)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Affected customer segment (all, new only, specific tier)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Business ctx:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Total customers (or MRR/ARR)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- CAC (to assess payback impact)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- NRR (to assess expansion ctx)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|You can provide estimates if you don't have exact numbers."
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**agt asks:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|"What type of pricing change are you considering?
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|1. **Price increase** — Raise prices for new customers, existing customers, or both
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|2. **New premium tier** — Add higher-priced tier with additional features
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|3. **Paid add-on** — Monetize a new or existing feature separately
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|4. **Usage-based pricing** — Charge for consumption (seats, API calls, storage, etc.)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|5. **Discount str** — Annual prepay discount, volume pricing, or promotional pricing
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|6. **Packaging change** — Rebundle features, change pricing metric, or tier restructure
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|Choose a number, or describe your specific pricing change."
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Based on selection, agt adapts questions:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**agt asks:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|"**Price increase details:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Current price: $___
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- New price: $___
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Increase: ___%
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Who is affected?**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|1. New customers only (grandfather existing)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|2. All customers (existing + new)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|3. Specific segment (e.g., SMB only, new plan only)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**When would this take effect?**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Immediately
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Next billing cycle
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Gradual rollout (test first)"
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**agt asks:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|"**Premium tier details:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Current top tier price: $___
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- New premium tier price: $___
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Key features in premium tier: [list]
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Expected adoption:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- What % of current customers might upgrade? ___%
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- What % of new customers might choose premium? ___%
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Cannibalization risk:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Will premium tier cannibalize current top tier?"
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**agt asks:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|"**Add-on details:**
