M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- OR conversion rate must stay above ___% (currently ___%)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- OR you need to reduce CAC to offset lower conversion
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Alternative strategies:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Instead of raising prices:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|1. **Improve retention** — Reduce churn from ___% to ___% (same revenue impact as price increase, lower risk)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|2. **Expand within base** — Increase NRR from ___% to ___% via upsells
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|3. **Reduce CAC** — More efficient acquisition (better than pricing)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**When to revisit pricing:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- After improving retention (churn <___%)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- After validating willingness-to-pay (WTP research)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- After competitive landscape changes
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**dec:** Hold pricing for now, focus on [retention / expansion / acquisition efficiency]."
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**agt offers:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|"Want to see what-if scenarios?
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|1. **Optimistic case** — Higher ARPU lift, lower churn
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|2. **Pessimistic case** — Lower ARPU lift, higher churn
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|3. **Breakeven analysis** — What churn rate makes this neutral?
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|Or ask any follow-up questions."
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**agt can provide:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Scenario modeling (optimistic/pessimistic/breakeven)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Sensitivity tables (if churn is X%, revenue impact is Y)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Comparison to alternative pricing strategies
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|See `examples/` folder for sample conversation flows. Mini examples below:
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Scenario:** 20% price increase for new customers only
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Current state:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- ARPU: $100/month
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Customers: 1,000
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- MRR: $100K
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Churn: 3%/month
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- New customers/month: 50
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Proposed change:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- New customer pricing: $120/month (+20%)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Existing customers: Grandfathered at $100
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Impact:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- New customer ARPU: $120 (+20%)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Churn risk: Low (existing protected)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Conversion impact: Minimal (<5% drop estimated)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Recommendation:** Implement. Net revenue impact +$12K/year with low risk.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Scenario:** 30% price increase for all customers
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Current state:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- ARPU: $50/month
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Customers: 5,000
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- MRR: $250K
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Churn: 5%/month (already high)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Proposed change:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- All customers: $65/month (+30%)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Impact:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- ARPU lift: +30% = +$75K MRR
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Churn risk: High (5% → 8% estimated)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Churn-driven loss: 3% × 5,000 × $65 = -$9.75K MRR/month
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Net impact:** +$75K - $9.75K = +$65K MRR (but accelerating churn problem)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Recommendation:** Don't change. Fix retention first (reduce 5% churn), then raise prices.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Scenario:** Add $500/month premium tier
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Current state:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Top tier: $200/month (500 customers)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- ARPA: $200
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Proposed change:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- New tier: $500/month with advanced features
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Expected adoption: 10% of current top tier (50 customers)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Impact:**
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Upsell revenue: 50 × ($500 - $200) = +$15K MRR
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- Cannibalization risk: Low (features justify premium)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|- NRR impact: Increases from 105% to 110%
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Recommendation:** Implement. Creates expansion path, minimal cannibalization risk.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Symptom:** "We'll raise prices 30% and make $X more!" (no churn modeling)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Consequence:** Churn wipes out revenue gains. Net impact negative.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Fix:** Model churn scenarios (conservative, base, optimistic). Factor churn-driven revenue loss into net impact.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Symptom:** "We're raising prices for everyone effective immediately"
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Consequence:** Massive churn spike from existing customers who feel betrayed.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Fix:** Grandfather existing customers. Raise prices for new customers only.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Symptom:** "We tested on 10 customers and it worked!"
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Consequence:** 10 customers isn't statistically significant. Results are noise.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Fix:** Test with large enough sample (100+ customers per cohort) for 60-90 days.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Symptom:** "We're raising prices because we need more revenue"
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Consequence:** Customers see price increase without corresponding value increase. Churn.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Fix:** Tie price increases to value improvements (new features, better support, outcomes delivered).
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Symptom:** "Higher ARPU is always better!"
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Consequence:** If conversion drops 30%, effective CAC increases dramatically. Payback period explodes.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Fix:** Calculate CAC payback impact. Higher ARPU with lower conversion might make payback worse, not better.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Symptom:** "30% discount for annual prepay!" (improves cash but destroys LTV)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Consequence:** Customers lock in low prices for a year. Revenue per customer decreases.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Fix:** Limit annual discounts to 10-15%. Balance cash flow improvement with LTV protection.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Symptom:** "cp raised prices, so should we"
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Consequence:** Your customers, value prop, and cost structure are different. What works for them may not work for you.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Fix:** Use cp as data points, not decisions. Make pricing decisions based on your unit economics.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Symptom:** "Let's A/B test 47 different price points!"
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Consequence:** Analysis paralysis. Spending months on 5% pricing optimizations while missing 50% growth opportunities elsewhere.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Fix:** Big pricing changes (tiers, packaging, add-ons) matter more than micro-optimizations. Start there.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Symptom:** "We're maximizing ARPU at acquisition"
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Consequence:** High upfront pricing prevents landing customers. Miss expansion opportunities.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Fix:** Consider "land and expand" str. Lower entry price, higher expansion revenue via upsells.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Symptom:** "We're raising prices next month" (no customer communication)
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Consequence:** Surprised customers churn. Poor reviews. Reputation damage.
M|finance-based-pricing-advisor|**Fix:** Communicate pricing changes 30-60 days in advance. Emphasize value, not just price.
